# planning-env-var-to-typed-cli-option-migration -- History

## v1.2.0 (2026-06-24)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus Issue #1526, R2 planning pass (third pass) -- fixed the last two R1-review minors
**Verification:** unverified (still a PLAN; never executed, no CI)

### What changed
- **VERIFY a typed-options object's TYPE at its construction site / `__init__`
  docstring -- do NOT infer it from the call's semantics (the dominant R2 lesson).**
  R1 reasoned "this is the implementer's learn step, so the options object must be
  `ImplementerOptions`" and was WRONG. Ground truth:
  `PostMergeProcessor.__init__(self, options_provider: Callable[[], Any])` is
  documented "Returns the current `CIDriverOptions`" -- the drive-green learn holds
  `CIDriverOptions`, not `ImplementerOptions`. Semantic intuition about which
  subsystem "owns" a call is an unreliable proxy for the concrete type threaded into
  it; read the holder's `__init__` signature/docstring or trace the constructor call.
- **Consequence: add the field to the type ACTUALLY held, not the family-typical
  one.** `CIDriverOptions` (not `ImplementerOptions`) gets the `learn_timeout` field,
  because that is the object `post_merge_processor` actually reads. The same knob name
  (`learn_timeout`) legitimately appears on TWO different options classes
  (`ImplementerOptions` for the implementer's own learn, `CIDriverOptions` for the
  drive-green learn) -- correct per-call-site granularity, NOT duplication to dedupe.
  This RESOLVES the R1 residual "post_merge_processor provider type" risk row.
- **Blast-radius counts drift across passes -- re-derive each pass, excluding
  build/ AND __pycache__.** The count went 36 (R0, worktree dupes) -> 18 (R1, wrong)
  -> 23 (R2, correct via
  `grep -rl <module> hephaestus/ tests/ | grep -v __pycache__ | grep -v build/ | wc -l`).
  A wrong-but-conservative number still misleads the sweep; enumerate the file LIST.
- **A non-default mock SENTINEL is the easy-to-miss test in a blast-radius sweep.**
  A test mocking `git_message_agent_timeout()` to return 120 (not even the real 300
  default) is missed by grepping default literals; grep the helper NAME across the
  whole test dir FIRST, then the literal sentinels.
- Converted the Failed-Attempts "post_merge_processor provider type" row from
  STILL-A-RISK to RESOLVED, and added a new row: "infer a call site's typed-options
  TYPE from the call's semantics -> WRONG TYPE."
- Added tags: provider-type-verification, options-type-inference. Kept all existing tags.
- Bumped version 1.1.0 -> 1.2.0. Verification remains `unverified` (still a plan).
- Two residual-risk items remain genuinely open: the surviving library-layer
  `HEPH_GH_CLI_TIMEOUT` (reviewer-bless, not author-resolvable) and drifting line
  numbers (no code executed).

### Why
R1 (PR #2819) left two open minors. R2 closed them: (a) the dominant fix was pinning
the `post_merge_processor` options-provider TYPE -- R1 had INFERRED it from the call's
"learn" semantics and guessed `ImplementerOptions`; reading the `__init__` docstring
showed it is `CIDriverOptions`, so the durable lesson is "verify the type at the
construction site, never infer it from what the call is about"; and (b) the
blast-radius count was re-derived (23, excluding build/). The existing skill was
amended (not duplicated) to fold both in.

